l awards apply to Division A only.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://beachsoccer.com/news/spain-down-russia-to-earn-belgrade-silverware |title= Spain down Russia to earn Belgrade silverware |work=beachsoccer.com |date=25 June 2017 |accessdate=26 June 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 97%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2 width=200|Stage Winners trophy\n!rowspan=2|\n!colspan=2 width=200|Top scorer(s)\n!width=200|Best player\n!width=200|Best goalkeeper\n|- align=center style=\"background: \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{beachsoccer|ESP}}<br /><small>(Division A)</small>||{{beachsoccer|EST}}<br /><small>(Division B)</small>||{{flagicon|ESP}} Llorenc Gomez<br />{{flagicon|FRA}} Anthony Barbotti || '''4 goals''' || {{flagicon|ESP}} Llorenc Gomez || {{flagicon|FRA}} Lorenzo Dupin\n|}\n\n== Stage 2 (Nazar\u00e9, 7\u20139 July) ==\nStage 2 was originally scheduled to take place in [[Sanxenxo]], [[Spain]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beachsoccer.com/news/the-euro-beach-soccer-league-bigger-and-better-than-ever |title=The Euro Beach Soccer League - bigger and better than ever!  |publisher=beachsoccer.com |date=27 March 2017 |accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref> but on 1 June, BSWW announced the stage was to be moved due to administrative issues, with Nazar\u00e9 becoming the new host city due to having successfully hosted the [[2017 Euro Winners Cup]] events, as well as being in close geographical proximity to the original hosts, Sanxenxo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beachsoccer.com/news/euro-beach-soccer-league-and-women-s-euro-beach-soccer-cup-move-to-nazare |title=Euro Beach Soccer League and Women\u2019s Euro Beach Soccer Cup move to Nazar\u00e9 |publisher=beachsoccer.com |date=1 June 2017 |accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nThere were no Division B fixtures during this stage.\n\n=== Division A ===\n''Matches are listed as local time in Nazar\u00e9, [[Western European Summer Time|WEST]] ([[UTC+1]])''\n\nAll matches took place at the ''Est\u00e1dio do Viveiro'' at the Praia de Nazar\u00e9, in tandem with the hosting of the [[2017 Women's Euro Beach Soccer Cup]]. The arena has a capacity of 1,600.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-de-praia/detalhe/champions-e-espetaculo-garantido.html |title=CHAMPIONS' \u00c9 ESPET\u00c1CULO GARANTIDO |publisher=record.pt |date=26 May 2017 |accessdate=28 June 2017 |language=Portuguese }}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Group 1====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 97%;\"\n|-\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip|Pos|Position}}\n!width=\"110\"|Team\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|Pld|Played}}\n!width=\"22\"|{{Tooltip|W|Wins}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|W+|Wins after extra time}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|W<small>P</small>|Wins on penalties}}\n!width=\"22\"|{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!width=\"25\"|{{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|Pts|Points}}\n!width=\"105\"|Notes\n|- style=\"background-color: #ccffcc;\"\n|1||align=left|{{beachsoccer|ESP}}\n|3||2||0||0||1||16||7||+9||'''6'''||Group Winners\n|-\n|2||align=left|{{beachsoccer|UKR}}\n|3||2||0||0||1||13||12||+1||'''6'''||rowspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n|3||align=left|{{beachsoccer|POL}}\n|3||1||0||1||1||9||8||+1||'''4'''\n|-\n|4||align=left|{{beachsoccer|GRE}}\n|3||0||0||0||3||7||18||\u201311||'''0'''\n|}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| date = 7 July 2017\n| time = 14:15\n| team1 = {{beachsoccer-rt|GRE}}\n| score = 5\u20136\n| report = [http://beachsoccerrussia.ru/tournaments/euroleague-2017/matches/4345 Report<small>(ru)</small>]\n| team2 = {{beachsoccer|UKR}}\n| goals1 = Triantafyllidis {{goal|3}}<br />Biris {{goal|4}}<br />Tsitaris {{goal|15||20}}<br />Karakasis {{goal|36}}\n| goals2 = {{goal|3}} Zavorotnyi<br />{{goal|12||24||32}} Glutskyi<br />{{goal|12||34}} Yevdokymov \n| stadium = \n| attendance = \n| referee = Giuseppe Sicurella ([[Italian Football Federation|Italy]])\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| date = 7 July 2017\