br />{{flagicon|BUL}} Pavel Adamov<br />{{flagicon|BUL}} Martin Velikov<br />{{flagicon|BUL}} Stanislav Dzhambazov<br />{{flagicon|HUN}} Richard Patocs\n|{{flagicon|BUL}} Filip Filipov<br />{{flagicon|ROM}} Bogdan Ciocanel<br />{{flagicon|MDA}} Victor Iordachi<br />{{flagicon|TUR}} Sem\u00edh T\u00fcrkmen<br />{{flagicon|ROM}} Gabriel Dobre<br />{{flagicon|BUL}} Kaloyan Tsvetkov<br />{{flagicon|LTU}} Viktor Bartosevic\n|'''2'''\n|{{beachsoccer|BUL}}\n|'''13'''\n|-\n!height=2 colspan=9|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''Second yellow cards''' {{Tooltip|{{sent off|2}}|Second yellow card}}\n|A\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|POR}} [[:pt:Bruno Torres (futebolista)|Bruno Torres]]<br />{{flagicon|RUS}} Anton Shkarin\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|POR}}<br />{{beachsoccer|RUS}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n|B\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|DEN}} Dan Storm\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|DEN}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n!height=2 colspan=9|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''Straight red cards''' {{Tooltip|{{sent off}}|Red card}}\n|A\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|SUI}} Tobias Steinemann\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|SUI}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n|B\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|TUR}} Erkan Anzafioglu<br />{{flagicon|LTU}} [[:lt:Aivaras Me\u0161kinis|Aivaras Me\u0161kinis]]<br />{{flagicon|ENG}} Taylor Humm<br />{{flagicon|MDA}} Leonid Podlesnov\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|TUR}}<br />{{beachsoccer|LTU}}<br />{{beachsoccer|ENG}}<br />{{beachsoccer|MDA}}\n|colspan=2|'''1'''\n|}\n<small>\n[http://beachsoccerrussia.ru/tournaments/euroleague-2017/statistic#fails Source]</small>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|50em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.beachsoccer.com/ Beach Soccer Worldwide] (organisers' official website)\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/news/the-euro-beach-soccer-league-bigger-and-better-than-ever Announcement & format]\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-belgrade-2017 Stage 1, Belgrade]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-sanxenxo-2017 Stage 2, Nazar\u00e9]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-moscow-2017 Stage 3, Moscow]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-siofok-2017 Stage 4, Si\u00f3fok]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-warnemunde-2017 Stage 5, Warnem\u00fcnde]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-superfinal-promotion-final-italy-2017 Superfinal]\n{{div col end}}\n\n{{Euro Beach Soccer League}}\n{{International Beach Soccer}}\n\n[[Category:Euro Beach Soccer League]]\n[[Category:2017 in beach soccer]]\n[[Category:2017 in Serbian sport]]\n[[Category:2017 in Portuguese sport]]\n[[Category:2017 in Russian sport]]\n[[Category:2017 in Hungarian sport]]\n[[Category:2017 in German sport]]\n[[Category:2017 in Italian sport]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name = Euro Beach Soccer League\n| year = 2017\n| dates = 23 June \u2013 17 September\n| other_titles =\n| image = 2017 EBSL Superfinal logo.png\n| size = \n| caption = Logo the Superfinal of the 2017 EBSL\n| num_teams = 27\n| confederations = 1\n| country = Serbia\n| country2 = Portugal\n| country3 = Russia\n| country4 = Hungary\n| country5 = Germany\n| country6 = Italy\n| venues = 6\n| cities = 6\n| champion_other = {{beachsoccer|RUS}}\n| count = 5\n| second_other = {{beachsoccer|POR}}\n| third_other = {{beachsoccer|ITA}}\n| fourth_other = {{beachsoccer|ESP}}\n| matches = 89\n| goals = 727\n| attendance =\n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| goalkeeper = \n| updated =\n| prevseason = [[2016 Euro Beach Soccer League|2016]]\n| nextseason = [[2018 Euro Beach Soccer League|2018]]\n}}\n{{Location map+ |Europe |width=380 |float=right |caption=Locations of the five stages and the Superfinal of the '''2017 Euro Beach Soccer League'''|places=\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=44.816667 |long=20.466667 |label=<small>''Stage 1'', '''[[Belgrade]]'''</small>|position=right|mark=Yellow_pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=55.75 |long=37.616667 |label=<small>''Stage 3'', '''[[Moscow]]'''</small>|position=right|mark=Yellow_pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=39.6 |long=-9.066667  |label=<small>''Stage 2'', '''[[Nazar\u00e9, Portugal|Nazar\u00e9]]'''</small>|position=right|mark=Yellow_pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=46.92393 |long=18.09012  |label=<small>''Stage 4'', '''[[Si\u00f3fok]]'''</small>|position=left|mark=Yellow_pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=54.166667 |long=12.083333  |label=<small>''Stage 5'', '''[[Warnem\u00fcnde]]'''</small>|position=right|mark=Yellow_pog.svg}}\n{{Location map~ |Europe |lat=41.2964 |long=13.2333 |label=<small>''Superfinal'', '''[[Terracina]]'''</small>|position=left|mark=Blue_pog.svg}}\n}}\nThe '''2017 [[Euro Beach Soccer League]] (EBSL)''' was the 20th edition of the annual, premier European competition in [[beach soccer]] contested between men's national teams, in a league and play-off format.\n\nThis season teams continued to take part in two divisions, the top tier (Division A) and the bottom tier (Division B). Twelve teams continued to contest Division A as in recent seasons, consisting of the top eleven finishers from last year plus [[Azerbaijan national beach soccer team|Azerbaijan]] who were promoted to the top tier. Division B was expanded to accommodate fifteen nations; the thirteen nations which did not gain promotion from last season, [[Lithuania national beach soccer team|Lithuania]] who made their debut, plus [[Romania national beach soccer team|Romania]] who were relegated from the top tier. No nations returned to the tournament after an absence from competing in recent years.\n\nThis season, in recognition of the 20th anniversary of the competition, additional matches were scheduled for a total of five ''stages'' of fixtures during the [[regular season]]. Each team from Division A played in two stages whilst each team from Division B played in one stage. During each stage the participating nations earned points for the overall league tables.\n\nAt the end of the regular season stages, according to the league tables, the eight best teams in Division A advanced to the [[post-season]] Superfinal to compete directly to become the winners of this year's EBSL. Meanwhile, the top seven teams in Division B (the stage winners and best runners-up) and the team ranked bottom of Division A played in the Promotion Final to try to earn a spot in Division A next year.\n\n[[Turkey national beach soccer team|Turkey]] were promoted to Division A after beating [[Estonia national beach soccer team|Estonia]] to claim the Promotion Final title. This sees Turkey return to the top flight for the first time since they were relegated from Division A in [[2011 Euro Beach Soccer League|2011]]. [[Greece national beach soccer team|Greece]] finished last in Division A and failed to defend their place in the Promotion Final and were therefore subsequently relegated to Division B, ending their four-year run in the top tier.\n\n[[Russia national beach soccer team|Russia]] won the league after a strong performance in the Superfinal, claiming their fifth EBSL crown to tie for first with [[Spain national beach soccer team|Spain]] and [[Portugal national beach soccer team|Portugal]] with the most titles in EBSL history. Defending champions [[Ukraine national beach soccer team|Ukraine]] were knocked out of title-winning contention in the group stage of the Superfinal, ultimately finishing seventh in the post-season event.\n\n== Calendar and locations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=\"200\"| Dates\n!width=\"120\"| Country\n!width=\"120\"| City\n!width=\"250\"| Stage\n|-\n| 23\u201325 June || {{flag|Serbia}} || [[Belgrade]] || Stage 1\n|-\n| 7\u20139 July || {{flag|Portugal}} || [[Nazar\u00e9, Portugal|Nazar\u00e9]] || Stage 2\n|-\n| 28\u201330 July || {{flag|Russia}} || [[Moscow]] || Stage 3\n|-\n| 11\u201313 August || {{flag|Hungary}} || [[Si\u00f3fok]] || Stage 4\n|-\n| 25\u201327 August || {{flag|Germany}} || [[Warnem\u00fcnde]] || Stage 5\n|-\n| 14\u201317 September|| {{flag|Italy}} || [[Terracina]] || Superfinal and Promotion Final\n|}\n\n==Teams==\n[[File:2017 EBSL map of nations.png|thumb|400px|{{legend|#67E863|Competing in '''Division A'''}} {{legend|#6085EF|Competing in '''Division B'''}} {{legend|#F36971|Competed in previous editions but not this year}} {{legend|#C3C3C3|Never competed in the EBSL}}]]\nThe following teams have entered this season, in the following divisions (12 in Division A, 15 in Division B).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theroonba.com/beachsoccer/men/fixtures.html|title=MEN'S BEACH SOCCER - FIXTURES|publisher=theroonba.com|accessdate=30 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe numbers in brackets show the European ranking of each team prior to the start of the season, out of 36 nations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beachsoccer.com/ranking/overall |title=OVERALL WORLD RANKING |publisher=beachsoccer.com |date=8 June 2017 |accessdate=8 June 2017 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170608011017/http://beachsoccer.com/ranking/overall |archivedate=8 June 2017 }}</ref>\n\n===Division A===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* {{beachsoccer|POR}} <small>(1st)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|RUS}} <small>(2nd)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|ITA}} <small>(3rd)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|SUI}} <small>(4th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|POL}} <small>(5th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|ESP}} <small>(6th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|UKR}} <small>(7th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|BLR}} <small>(9th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|FRA}} <small>(11th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|GER}} <small>(12th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|AZE}}<sup>'''[[#1|1]]'''</sup> <small>(14th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|GRE}} <small>(15th)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Division B===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* {{beachsoccer|HUN}} <small>(8th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|ENG}} <small>(10th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|CZE}} <small>(13th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|TUR}} <small>(16th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|ROM}}<sup>'''[[#2|2]]'''</sup> <small>(17th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|EST}} <small>(18th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|MDA}} <small>(19th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|NED}} <small>(20th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|NOR}} <small>(21st)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|SRB}} <small>(22nd)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|BUL}} <small>(24th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|KAZ}} <small>(25th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|DEN}} <small>(26th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|AND}} <small>(27th)</small>\n* {{beachsoccer|LTU}}<sup>'''[[#3|3]]'''</sup> <small>(28th)</small>\n{{div col end}}\n<small>'''Notes:'''\n:<div id=\"1\">1. Promoted from Division B at the end of the [[2016 Euro Beach Soccer League|2016 season]]\n:<div id=\"2\">2. Relegated from Division A at the end of the 2016 season\n:<div id=\"3\">3. Teams making their debut</small>\n\n== Stage 1 (Belgrade, 23\u201325 June) ==\n''Matches are listed as local time in Belgrade, [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+2]])''\n\nAll matches took place at the ''National Beach Soccer Stadium'' at [[Ada Ciganlija]], with a capacity of 2,500.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://beachsoccer.rs/stadion/ |title= Stadion |work= Beach Soccer Serbia |accessdate=21 June 2017 |language = Serbian}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Division A ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 97%;\"\n|-\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip|Pos|Position}}\n!width=\"110\"|Team\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|Pld|Played}}\n!width=\"22\"|{{Tooltip|W|Wins}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|W+|Wins after extra time}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|W<small>P</small>|Wins on penalties}}\n!width=\"22\"|{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!width=\"25\"|{{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}\n!width=\"18\"|{{Tooltip|Pts|Points}}\n!width=\"105\"|Notes\n|- style=\"background-color: #ccffcc;\"\n|1||align=left|{{beachsoccer|ESP}}\n|3||2||0||0||1||10||9||+1||'''6'''||Group Winners\n|-\n|2||align=left|{{beachsoccer|FRA}}\n|3||1||1||0||1||13||11||+2||'''5'''||rowspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n|3||align=left|{{beachsoccer|RUS}}\n|3||1||0||0||2||6||9||\u20133||'''3'''\n|-\n|4