ext-align:left| {{flagicon|ROM}} Gabriel Dobre || 3 || rowspan=4|3\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left| {{flagicon|DEN}} Klaus Ryding || 3\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left| {{flagicon|ROM}} Bogdan Ciocanel || 6\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left| {{flagicon|HUN}} Viktor Fekete || 7\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n<small>[http://beachsoccerrussia.ru/tournaments/euroleague-2017/statistic#assistents Source]</small>\n\n<small>'''Note:''' The source of these assists stats does not explain what system was used to determine the award of an assist. The total no. of assists recorded is 270 but 727 goals were scored. The discrepancy of the source not recording an assist for every goal scored may be due to a system in use such as [[Assist (football)#FIFA|FIFAs assists system]] - (regardless of who made the final pass to the scorer, no assist is awarded when the scorer ultimately lays the goal on for him/herself via a dribble, solo run etc, scores after intercepting an opponent's pass etc.). However since the system in use is not explained, note that assists may simply of gone undocumented.</small>\n\n===Discipline===\nThe following table lists the players and teams who received the most penalties for disciplinary infringements in each division in both the regular and post season events.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 93%;\"\n|-\n|-\n!Category\n!width=30|Div.\n!rowspan=9|\n!width=200 colspan=2|Player(s)\n!width=30|#\n!rowspan=9|\n!width=150|Team(s)\n!width=30|#\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''Most yellow cards {{Tooltip|{{yel}}|Yellow card}}\n|A\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|SUI}} Dejan Stankovi\u0107<br>{{flagicon|POL}} Konrad Kubiak<br>{{flagicon|ITA}} Gabriele Gori\n|'''4'''\n|{{beachsoccer|SUI}}\n|'''18'''\n|-\n|B\n|{{flagicon|SRB}} [[Nikola Valenti\u0107]]<br>{{flagicon|SRB}} Vojislav Trajkovic<br>{{flagicon|EST}} Ragnar Rump<br>{{flagicon|BUL}} Pavel Adamov<br>{{flagicon|BUL}} Martin Velikov<br>{{flagicon|BUL}} Stanislav Dzhambazov<br>{{flagicon|HUN}} Richard Patocs\n|{{flagicon|BUL}} Filip Filipov<br>{{flagicon|ROM}} Bogdan Ciocanel<br>{{flagicon|MDA}} Victor Iordachi<br>{{flagicon|TUR}} Sem\u00edh T\u00fcrkmen<br>{{flagicon|ROM}} Gabriel Dobre<br>{{flagicon|BUL}} Kaloyan Tsvetkov<br>{{flagicon|LTU}} Viktor Bartosevic\n|'''2'''\n|{{beachsoccer|BUL}}\n|'''13'''\n|-\n!height=2 colspan=9|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''Second yellow cards''' {{Tooltip|{{sent off|2}}|Second yellow card}}\n|A\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|POR}} [[:pt:Bruno Torres (futebolista)|Bruno Torres]]<br>{{flagicon|RUS}} Anton Shkarin\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|POR}}<br>{{beachsoccer|RUS}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n|B\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|DEN}} Dan Storm\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|DEN}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n!height=2 colspan=9|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''Straight red cards''' {{Tooltip|{{sent off}}|Red card}}\n|A\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|SUI}} Tobias Steinemann\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|SUI}}\n|'''1'''\n|-\n|B\n|colspan=2|{{flagicon|TUR}} Erkan Anzafioglu<br>{{flagicon|LTU}} [[:lt:Aivaras Me\u0161kinis|Aivaras Me\u0161kinis]]<br>{{flagicon|ENG}} Taylor Humm<br>{{flagicon|MDA}} Leonid Podlesnov\n|'''1'''\n|{{beachsoccer|TUR}}<br>{{beachsoccer|LTU}}<br>{{beachsoccer|ENG}}<br>{{beachsoccer|MDA}}\n|colspan=2|'''1'''\n|}\n<small>\n[http://beachsoccerrussia.ru/tournaments/euroleague-2017/statistic#fails Source]</small>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|50em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.beachsoccer.com/ Beach Soccer Worldwide] (organisers' official website)\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/news/the-euro-beach-soccer-league-bigger-and-better-than-ever Announcement & format]\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-belgrade-2017 Stage 1, Belgrade]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-sanxenxo-2017 Stage 2, Nazar\u00e9]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-moscow-2017 Stage 3, Moscow]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-siofok-2017 Stage 4, Si\u00f3fok]\n* [http://beachsoccer.com/events/euro-beach-soccer-league-warnemunde-2