f>{{cite news|title=Jacque Vaugh added to Spurs front office|url=https://www.nba.com/spurs/jacque-vaughn-added-spurs-front-office|publisher=NBA Media Ventures, LLC|website=NBA.com|date=September 22, 2015|access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> He was hired as [[Kenny Atkinson]]'s top assistant coach for the [[Brooklyn Nets]] prior to the 2016\u201317 season,<ref>{{cite news|title=Brooklyn Nets Finalize Coaching Staff|url=http://www.nba.com/nets/news/2016/07/05/brooklyn-nets-finalize-coaching-staff|work=NBA.com|date=July 5, 2016|accessdate=July 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Report: Nets hiring Jacque Vaughn as lead assistant coach|url=https://nba.nbcsports.com/2016/05/02/report-nets-hiring-jacque-vaughn-as-lead-assistant-coach/|publisher=NBC Sports|website=nbcsports.com|date=May 2, 2016|access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> and was promoted to interim head coach position in March 2020 following Atkinson's mid-season departure.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brooklyn Nets and Kenny Atkinson Mutually Agree to Part Ways|url=https://www.nba.com/nets/news/2020/03/07/brooklyn-nets-and-kenny-atkinson-mutually-agree-to-part-ways|publisher=NBA Media Ventures, LLC|website=NBA.com|date=March 7, 2020|access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> \n\n===Head coaching record===\n{{NBA coach statistics legend}}\n{{NBA coach statistics start}}\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2012\u201313 Orlando Magic season|Orlando]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2012}}\n| 82 || 20 || 62 || {{Winning percentage|20|62}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|5th in [[Southeast Division (NBA)|Southeast]] || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Missed playoffs\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2013\u201314 Orlando Magic season|Orlando]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{nbay|2013}}\n| 82 || 23 || 59 || {{Winning percentage|23|59}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"|5th in Southeast || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Missed playoffs\n|-\n| style=\"text-